data.title: IRMPD Spectroscopy Sheds New (Infrared) Light on the Sulfate Pattern of Carbohydrates
data.meta_description: IR spectroscopy of gas-phase ions is proposed to resolve positional isomers of sulfated carbohydrates. Mass spectrometric fingerprints and gas-phase vibrational spectra in the near and mid-IR regions were obtained for sulfated monosaccharides, yielding unambiguous signatures of sulfated isomers. We …
